# ArtCade — architecture authority

Canonical product and architecture contract. Outranks generic UI advice.

- **Product UI:** sibling repo `ArtCade_Editor_RmlUi` (native RmlUi).
- **This repo:** `runtime-cpp` + optional headless `artcade_editor_core`.
- **Forbidden debt:** obsolete authoring UI stacks — do not reintroduce,
  document as active product, or adapt.

## Authority (one source each)

| Concern | Owner |
|---|---|
| Persistent project | `ProjectDocument` / `ProjectDoc` |
| Workspace (RmlUi editor) | `EditorState` in ArtCade_Editor_RmlUi |
| Layout chrome only | `EditorUiState` / panel-local |
| Runtime during Play | `PlaySession` |
| Loaded textures | cache derived, never authoritative |

## Mutation flow

UI → Intent / Command → Coordinator → ProjectDocument → DomainChange → targeted invalidation.

- Presentation never mutates `ProjectDocument` directly.
- No polling sync bus or `RefreshAll()` per frame.
- Play materializes once from the document; no reverse-sync on Stop.

## Explicit non-goals

- Parallel authoring stacks
- QML/Qt revival
- Filename-as-identity
- Implicit GameVariable creation
- Untyped call-by-name bridges
